        <div type="letter">
            <div type="text">
                <opener>
                    <placeName><hi rend="print">Down, | Beckenham, Kent.</hi></placeName>
                    <date>Jan 23 1873</date>
                    <salute>My dear Sir</salute>
                </opener>
                <div type="transcription">
                     
<p>Although my memory does not aid me, I have no doubt that the description in small type of the wood-cut is correct, &amp; that I have in the two places in the large type referred to the wrong vertebra; so that it is as you suppose. You are a most conscientious editor &amp; are as careful as I am apt to be careless—<ref target="#foot.f1"/></p>
<p>yours very sincerely | Ch. Darwin</p> 
                </div>
            </div>

        </div>

        

        

        <div type="footnotes">
            <note xml:id="foot.f1">See <ref target="./DCP-LETT-8746.xml" resp="#mjhawkins">letter from J. V. Carus, 21 January 1873</ref>; Carus had sent some corrections to <ref target="../bibliographies/bibl_7951.xml" resp="#mjhawkins"><hi rend="italic">Variation</hi></ref>.</note>
        </div>        
            
